B RAD10 storage</li><li>500GB/month data transfer</li><li>XenServer</li><li>1x IPv4 + 1x IPv6</li></ul><p>On their home page it says their servers are in New York City metro area. Pretty awesome spec \u2014 only if you can order one. I have just tried and it displays it is currently out of stock.</p><p>Domain has been registered for a month to a New York based company \u201cNeutrino Networks\u201d. Although their servers are in NY their website is at WebFaction in Houston TX. In the email, Dylan also left a signature that says \u201cNeutrino AB\u201d \u2014 which indicates that it might be a Swedish company.</p><p><span id=\"more-974\"></span></p><p><b>Update</b>: Dylan has sent me the following info</p><blockquote><p>Open letter to anyone that inquired about VPS services:</p><p>We kind of had some teething problems with the new XenServer VPSes, most of us are Virtuozzo guys \u2013 not really Xen. Had a batch of drives fail, degraded RAID arrays, some issues with controllers and Citrix, and ran into API \u201cissues\u201d when coding our inhouse control panel plus some other stuff.</p><p>I am asking Lowendadmin to take off the links/coupon for now, we will be delaying the release of VPS service for a bit until all the kinks are properly worked out.</p><p>We will be revamping the entire system (or maybe changing to VMware or Xensource) and opening up a free beta testing period, which probably should<br>\nhave been done in the first place, to the public in the near future for about two to three months to make sure there are no issues before going production again. Don\u2019t have an ETA right now.</p><p>I\u2019m sorry for inconveniencing all that have wanted to order. We have actually only gotten payment from about four people before disabling orders, all of those that paid have been fully refunded plus 15% for their trouble.</p><p>Again, apologies for the trouble.</p><p>Dyl</p></blockquote><p>Well. All I can suggest to other hosting providers is \u2014 <b>do not</b> 